Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Meanwhile, trim the @green beans{80%g}. Cut into thirds.

Pour the boiled water into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Boil the @egg noodle nest{125%g}, ~{4%minutes}. Once cooked, drain and run under cold water.

Meanwhile, heat a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, fry the @British beef mince{240%g} and green beans, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Break up the mince as it cooks, then drain the fat. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Next, add the @coleslaw mix{120%g} to the pan. Stir-fry, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in the @hoisin sauce{64%g}, @Szechuan paste{1%sachet}, @sweet chilli sauce{48%g} and @water{50%ml}.

Bring to the boil. Simmer, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Add the cooked noodles. Toss to coat in the sauce, ~{1%minute}. Add a splash of water if needed.

Share the beef noodles between your bowls.

Enjoy!